using UnityEngine;

public class RotateObject : MonoBehaviour
{
    public float rotationSpeed = 10f;

    private void Update()
    {
        // Rotate the gameObject around the Y-axis
        transform.Rotate(Vector3.up, rotationSpeed * Time.deltaTime);
    }
}


To use this script, follow these steps:

1. Create a new C# script in your Unity project and name it "RotateObject" (or any other name you prefer).
2. Open the script in your preferred code editor.
3. Copy and paste the above code into the script file.
4. Save the script and go back to the Unity editor.
5. Attach the script to the gameObject you want to rotate by dragging and dropping it onto the gameObject in the Unity hierarchy.
6. Adjust the "rotationSpeed" variable in the Inspector to control the speed of rotation. Positive values rotate counter-clockwise, while negative values rotate clockwise.
7. Press the Play button in Unity to see the gameObject rotate over time.

This script uses the `Update` method, which is called every frame, to rotate the gameObject around the Y-axis using the `transform.Rotate` method. The rotation speed is controlled by the `rotationSpeed` variable, which can be adjusted in the Inspector.

